               <p>about two or three o'clock, I met the prisoners coming along the Edgeware-road—I took them, and found the bag under Bond's waistcoat, and the violin strings in Conway's pocket-Bond said he brought the bag from home.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Bond's Defence</hi>. I picked it up in the Crown and Anchor booth—there was nothing in it.</p>
